##  Who we are:

Sizztech predicts the future of cities. Sizztech is a global leader in solving
complex urban design and urban growth challenges. Sizztech is the developer of
Forecaz, an urban growth modelling platform. Forecaz utilises AI and spatial
technologies to analyse the impacts of current and alternative land use
scenarios and evaluate their effects on future urban development.

Sizztech is based in the Queensland Government Innovation Precinct in
Brisbaneâ€™s Fortitude Valley. Our customers include local government
authorities, the federal and state governments, and utility providers.

Sizztech is about to undertake a significant re-architecture and upgrade to
the Forecaz platform due to customer demand.

##  Who we are looking for:

We are seeking a mid-level .NET Developer looking for the opportunity to
advance their career and grow their skills in AI and ML, .NETCore and
geospatial frameworks. We want someone who is excited to work in a
collaborative and flat-structured team environment. You will be comfortable
bringing new ideas to the team and contributing to delivering our enhanced
version of Forecaz.

As a .NET Developer in our team, you should:

  * Been exposed/worked on .NET software development projects (preferably for 2 to 3 years or more) 
  * Want exposure and grow your skills relating to 
    * Geospatial technologies 
    * Artificial Intelligence (AI) 
    * Machine Learning (ML) 
  * Have a passion for helping our customers get the best out of our software. 

##  ** What skills and experience should you have: **

  * Experience or exposure to the following ** Back-end ** languages and frameworks: 
    * C# ( ** required ** ) 
    * Entity Framework ( ** required ** ) 
    * SQL ( ** required ** ) 
    * ASP.NET 
    * .NET Core 
    * Python 
    * Or other comparable languages 
  * Experience or exposure to the following ** Front-end ** languages and frameworks: 
    * Vue 
    * React 
    * Tailwind CSS 
    * JavaScript 
  * Supporting customers using an ITIL service management tool 
  * Reviewing, cleaning and uploading data to a database (SQL or equivalent) 
  * Writing test cases (using industry best practices) 
  * Understanding of Agile/Scrum methodologies/development frameworks 
  * Use of Agile management tools such as: 
    * GIT 
    * Azure DevOps 
    * TeamCity 
    * Octopus 
    * Or other Deployment Pipelines (CI/CD) 
  * Use of Azure/AWS cloud-based environments 
  * Great written and verbal communication skills. 
  * Command Query Responsibility Segregation patterns (CQRS) 
  * Domain Driven Design 

##  Working at Sizztech offers you:

  * Flexible working conditions with hybrid office and work-from-home available. 
  * Working on a world-leading technology platform in a modern and collaborative environment. 
  * End-of-trip facilities with bicycle parking and showers with a free towel service. 
  * A competitive salary based on the applicant's level of capabilities and experience. 
  * Regular tech meetups and social events located in the building, plus other team events. 

This role is based in Brisbane Qld and is only open to applicants who have
unrestricted work rights in Australia.

Sizztech is dedicated to attracting and developing our team regardless of
gender identity, ethnicity, sexual orientation, disability and age.
Applications from all sectors of the community are encouraged.

